snippet.textDisplay: I love the fact that chip manufacturers are aiming for 2nm. When I was doing my physics degree - my uni still had its own clean room so we could make our own (very simple) ICs. At that time Intel was on a 90nm process so it didn't seem too silly to do the maths (based on the technology we had available at the time) to show that, at 25nm, we wouldn't be able to make transistors any smaller...  This is one of those occasions where being wrong turns out to be a really good thing.

snippet.textDisplay: FYI : 2nm is not the transistor size, ever since 40nm the smallest "feature" a certain technology has been the spacing between some of the layers and not the polysilicon that makes the gate.
